2021/06/04 Suggestions:

Use a json file to load the touch screen parameters so they can just double click the app to load it 

[x] randomly seed agents in the cell, different orientations (small offsets) to make it so that they don't go along the diagonal

Make a separate a ros websocket launch file (so it doesn't have to be closed and reopened)

worth slowing it down for training (needs to be slower for a person starting)

layering colors -> stronger attractions vs. flat colors

bigger environment

training with static biomodal or multimodal so people can see how capture works, how their agents could be captured.

Initial training environment has no adversaries, just targets to drive to or obstacles to steer around.

Erase? with white color; add button

[x] Keep the brush size as max